Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no
need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle},
then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a
single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. While the pan gets
hot, season the @chicken breasts{2%British} with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Once hot, lay in the chicken and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes} each side.
While the chicken cooks, trim the @green beans{150%g}. Halve, peel and thinly
slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Once browned, pop the chicken on a baking tray and roast on the shelf below the
potatoes until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes} - don't wash your pan, you still
need it!

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When cooked, remove from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a
couple of minutes.

Meanwhile, pop the @BBQ sauce{64%ml}, @honey{15%ml} and @water{1%tbsp} per person
into a #bowl{} and stir together.

Pop your frying pan back on medium high heat (no need to wash it). Add a drizzle
of oil and the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and stir fry until starting to
brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the green beans to the bacon, season with salt and
pepper. Stir fry until tender and slightly charred, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the
shallot and stir fry with the beans until the shallot is soft and golden,
~{2-3%minutes}, then add the garlic and stir fry for ~{1%minute}. Pop on your
plates and cover with foil to keep warm.

Remove the pan from the heat and pour in the sauce and stir well. Bring to a
bubble and allow the sauce to reduce slightly. Once the chicken is cooked, add it
to the pan and roll it in the sauce. Serve on your plates with the beans. Serve
the wedges alongside and spoon any remaining sauce in the pan onto the chicken.
Enjoy!

> MOD: If you've added bacon lardons to your recipe, before you add the green beans
> to your pan in the step above, add the bacon lardons and stir fry until starting
> to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the green beans to the bacon and continue with the
> recipe as instructed.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.